# Frontend Conventions

- Use functional components with TypeScript.
- State management: TanStack Query for server state, React state/context for UI state.
- Styling: Tailwind CSS utility classes + shadcn/ui components. No CSS modules or styled-components.
- Forms: React Hook Form + Zod resolvers using schemas from `@bdaily/shared`.

## File Organization

- `src/components/` — reusable UI components
- `src/components/ui/` — shadcn/ui primitives
- `src/pages/` — route-level page components
- `src/hooks/` — custom hooks (data fetching, business logic)
- `src/lib/` — utilities, API client, constants

## Patterns

- Co-locate component-specific hooks and types with the component.
- Prefer composition over prop drilling — use context sparingly.
- All API calls go through the typed API client in `src/lib/api.ts`, never raw `fetch`.
